quran[24]{c,v,t,f}:
  55,17,"Lord of the two Easts and Lord of the two Wests."
  55,18,"So which of your Lord’s marvels do you<a class=""sup""><sup>dl </sup></a>disbelieve in?"
  55,19,"He merged the two waters{1}, converging together;",footnotes:1:Either the fresh water of rivers and the salty water of seas, or the waters of two different oceans.
  55,20,"between them is a barrier which they do not overrun."
  55,21,"So which of your Lord’s marvels do you<a class=""sup""><sup>dl </sup></a>disbelieve in?"
  55,22,"From them <span class=""h"">come out<sup foot_note=""81256"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">pearls and corals</span>."
  55,23,"So which of your Lord’s marvels do you<a class=""sup""><sup>dl </sup></a>disbelieve in? "
  55,24,"His are the running ships, <span class=""h"">whose sails are raised<sup foot_note=""81257"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>in the sea like banners{2}.",footnotes:2:The Arabic word used is Aʻlāmwhich also means ‘tall mountains’.
  55,25,"So which of your Lord’s marvels do you<a class=""sup""><sup>dl </sup></a>disbelieve in?"
  55,26,"Everyone upon it{1}is bound to perish,",footnotes:1:The earth.
  55,27,"and all that remains is your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord’s Countenance, the Possessor of majesty and nobility."
  55,28,"So which of your Lord’s marvels do you<a class=""sup""><sup>dl </sup></a>disbelieve in?"
  55,29,"Everyone in the heavens and the earth asks Him; every day He is bringing about a matter."
  55,30,"So which of your Lord’s marvels do you<a class=""sup""><sup>dl </sup></a>disbelieve in?"
  55,31,"<span class=""h"">We<sup foot_note=""81260"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">will attend</span>to you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>, O two huge communities<a class=""sup""><sup>c </sup></a>."
  55,32,"So which of your Lord’s marvels do you<a class=""sup""><sup>dl </sup></a>disbelieve in?"
  55,33,"O society of unseen beings and humans, if you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>can penetrate the bounds of the heavens and the earth then go ahead and penetrate; you will never penetrate except with authority{1}.",footnotes:1:The Qur’anic style involves leaving part of the meaning to be deduced by the listener; Ar-Rāzi and other exegetes said that this may mean ‘except with authority from God’, or ‘except with authority that you do not have’.
  55,34,"So which of your Lord’s marvels do you<a class=""sup""><sup>dl </sup></a>disbelieve in?"
  55,35,"Flares of fire<span class=""h"">, and brass<sup foot_note=""81262"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>, will be sent upon you<a class=""sup""><sup>dl </sup></a>, and you will not find help<i class=""s"">. </i>"
  55,36,"So which of your Lord’s marvels do you<a class=""sup""><sup>dl </sup></a>disbelieve in?"
  55,37,"And when the sky ruptures and becomes rose-colored like oil—"
  55,38,"so which of your Lord’s marvels do you<a class=""sup""><sup>dl </sup></a>disbelieve in?"
  55,39,"On that day neither any human nor unseen being{1}is asked about his misdeeds.",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is jānn(the singular of jinn), which is an unseen being that is accountable for its actions.
  55,40,"So which of your Lord’s marvels do you<a class=""sup""><sup>dl </sup></a>disbelieve in?"
